- `a ∈ A` (`h3`)
- `f a = b` (`h4`)

To construct the bijection between `A \ {a}` and `B \ {b}`:
1. For the forward direction: take `x ∈ A \ {a}`. Then `x ∈ A` and `x ≠ a`. Since `f` is one-to-one on `A`, `f x ≠ f a` (which is `b`). So `f x ∈ B \ {b}`.
2. For the reverse direction: take `y ∈ B \ {b}`. Then `y ∈ B` and `y ≠ b`. Since `image f A = B`, there exists `x ∈ A` such that `f x = y`. Since `y ≠ b`, `f x ≠ f a`, so `x ≠ a`. Thus `x ∈ A \ {a}`.

